"{\"uid\": \"lgbtqnation.com-2024-08-paris-mayor-drops-f-bombs-on-anti-lgbtq-critics-of-olympic-opening-ceremonies\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"French Mayor Anne Hidalgo had some choice words for Trump and other far-right critics of the queer-inclusive opening events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999650773729556, \"rank\": 3.062140735449484e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 13, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.229584617349478e-14, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some choice words\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"other far-right critics\", \"from\": 62, \"to\": 85}, {\"ngram\": \"the queer-inclusive opening events\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne Hidalgo - the mayor of Paris, France, the host city of the 2024 Olympic Summer Games - dropped several f-bombs on far-right conservatives who ignorantly blasted the Olympic's opening ceremonies for allegedly \\\"mocking Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 154, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 3.143460565558043e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999389115497812, \"rank\": 3.14774185299054e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999978708729, \"rank\": 2.128167112216189e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 138}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"the host city\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Summer Games\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 215}, {\"ngram\": \"several f-bombs\", \"from\": 226, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"far-right conservatives\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic's opening ceremonies\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conservative critics claimed that a segment of the ceremonies representing a Dionysian feast - with a lesbian DJ and drag performers - was a mockery of \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" a regularly re-imagined religious scene painted by gay Italian Renaissance artist Leonardo Da Vinci.\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.7623511969666132e-11, \"text\": \"Dionysian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\"}, {\"begin\": 590, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"score\": 0.9952671430411102, \"rank\": 0.004755352551414889, \"text\": \"Italian Renaissance\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\"}, {\"begin\": 590, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"score\": 0.9952671430411102, \"rank\": 0.004755352551414889, \"text\": \"Italian Renaissance\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\"}, {\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.647397590925893e-21, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.414776242486067e-37, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Conservative critics\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"a segment\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremonies\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 425}, {\"ngram\": \"a lesbian DJ\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"drag performers\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 532}, {\"ngram\": \"a regularly re-imagined religious scene\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Religious and anti-LGBTQ+ leaders worldwide blasted the segment, includingHouse Speaker Mike Johnson (R-LA)and former United States President Donald Trump.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_presidential_election\", \"score\": 0.9980462558769823, \"rank\": 0.0019575687110498846, \"text\": \"United States President\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_presidential_election\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_presidential_election\"}, {\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1799198872963886e-15, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Religious and anti-LGBTQ+ leaders\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 670}, {\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"R-LA)and\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But while the ceremony organizers have denied any intention to recreate \\\"The Last Supper\\\" or offend others, Hidalgo was much more blunt, saying in a recent interview, \\\"F**k the reactionaries, f**k this far-right, f**k all of those who would like to lock us into a war of all against all.\\\"\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.961236568053993e-16, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony organizers\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"any intention\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"a recent interview\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"the reactionaries\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"a war\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo also said she was proud of the way that the opening ceremony presented Paris to the world,according toPolitico.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1165, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 3.143460565558043e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hidalgo\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"toPolitico\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She acknowledged, \\\"There is both admiration for this incredible city, which not many people understand, and at the same time orchestration of a hatred of Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 3.143460565558043e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"both admiration\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"this incredible city\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"not many people\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"orchestration\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"a hatred\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paris is the city of all freedoms, the city of refuge for LGBTQI+ people, the city where people live together,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 3.143460565558043e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"all freedoms\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"refuge\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQI+ people\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The far right's messaging has been crushed by these Games and by the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1581, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The far right's messaging\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Something incredibly positive is happening.\\\"\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Something\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the segment, lesbian DJ Barbara Butch wore a silver headdress that looked like a halo, and was surrounded by drag performers, dancers, and other performers as she DJed.\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver headdress\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"a halo\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"drag performers\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"other performers\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1790}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The performers then walked on the runway, showcasing French fashions and style.\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999650773729556, \"rank\": 3.062140735449484e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The performers\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1818}, {\"ngram\": \"the runway\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1844}, {\"ngram\": \"style\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Near the segment's climax, a man with blue skin, an orange beard, and a body and crown covered in leaves and flowers appeared on a silver platter to join the performers.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the segment's climax\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1909}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"blue skin\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"an orange beard\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"a body\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"crown\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"leaves\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"flowers\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver platter\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"the performers\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2052}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV Olympic officials have repeatedly stated that the performance was not a recreation ofThe Last Supperbut was actually a tableau of a Dionysian feast.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.6426670487454865, \"rank\": 0.5175241138652886, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2091, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.549411643774329e-30, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.7623511969666132e-11, \"text\": \"Dionysian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollonian_and_Dionysian\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The interpretation\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV Olympic officials\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2235}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"a recreation ofThe\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2306}, {\"ngram\": \"Last Supperbut\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"a tableau\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the opening ceremonies, said, \\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.6328319815618637, \"rank\": 0.5801982660864258, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artistic director\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremonies\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2430}, {\"ngram\": \"My wish\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of all, I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2536}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly said he hoped for the performance to be a tribute to diversity, and that the runway-table during the segment was intended a \\\"tribute to feasting and French gastronomy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999650773729556, \"rank\": 3.062140735449484e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"a tribute\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2652}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2665}, {\"ngram\": \"the runway-table\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"tribute\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Villarreal